This process or steps for using data science to solve a particular problem is called the data science life cycle.



The purpose of this learning activity is to introduce you to the various phases of the data science life cycle.



## The Data Science Life Cycle



I have adapted the steps of the data science life cycle from the cross-industry standard process for data mining - CRISP-DM.



CRISP-DM is an open standard process model that describes common approaches used by data mining experts.



This model was conceived in 1996, and it's still one of the most widely used data science models.



The phases of the Data Science Life Cycle are:



1. Business Problem Definition

2. Data Collection

3. Data Preparation

4. Exploratory Data Analysis

5. Modelling (using Machine Learning Algorithms)

6. Evaluation (in business terms)

7. Model Deployment



The 7 steps I'm using in this course are shown below. In this course, we'll not do the last 2 steps.



