d. Replace outliers with the median

One strategy is to replace outliers with the median value in that particular column, as shown in the code below.



In the code, we set up a for loop to process a list of columns to replace outliers with the median value. The code is very similar to the previous one, except for the last statement, which does the replacement. We use the where() function from numpy to do the replacement.  The where() function takes 3 arguments separated by commas:



condition for filtering the rows to be replaced -  i.e., all the rows in the particular column with values less than the lower cut-off point or greater than the upper cut-off point

median value - this was calculated at the start of the loop

column for which the values are to be replaced

To make the changes permanent, we assign the returned value back to the same column of the data frame.



After the loop, we check the results by invoking the describe() method on the data frame or its transpose, depending on your liking. Please note that this statement is outside the for loop. As such, it should not be indented from the left margin.



