8. Scikit-Learn's classification report



### 8. Scikit-Learn's classification report



After having seen a number of performance metrics, which ones do we use?



If the dataset is ***balanced***, that is  we have more or less equal number of observations for both class 0 and 1, we can safely use the ***accuracy score***.



However, if the dataset is ***unbalanced***, that is, we have more observations for one class than the other, then using the ***accuracy score*** is ***misleading***. A better measure is the ***F1 score***.



***Furthermore***, if the dataset is ***unbalanced***,  and ***one class*** is ***more important*** than the other, then compute the ***F1 score per class*** and choose the model with the best f1 score for the particular class.



An example is fraud detection, in which it is mode important to correctly label  fraudulent classes than label non-fraudulent cases. Please note that F1 scores can be computed per class as well. ***Sklearn's classification report*** also calculates ***F1 scores per class***.



