## Label encoding of categorical variables



As explained before,  any column that contains word labels should be replaced with numeric labels. For example,



***no and yes*** should be replaced with with ***0 an 1***, ***red/blue/green*** with ***0, 1 and 2***, ***normal/high/very high*** with ***0, 1, and 2,*** etc.



One issue with replacing word labels with numbers is that  some algorithms think that there is some explicit ordering between the numbers. Especially when there are more than two numbers. They might think that 1 is greater than 0



and 2 is greater than 1, etc. However, this is not the case as the numbers are just category codes. I'll show you how to address this issue later with one-hot encoding.



